HEADWORD: Drastic
<hw>Dras"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to
do, act: cf. F. <ets>drastique</ets>. See <er>Drama</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Acting rapidly and violently; efficacious;
powerful; -- opposed to <contr>bland</contr>; <as>as, <ex>drastic</ex>
purgatives</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
violent purgative. See <er>Cathartic</er>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

